WHEREAS, Mr. Durham was most notably a loving husband, father, grandfather,
and great-grandfather; he cherished his family and found immense joy in the company of his
great-grandchildren; and
WHEREAS, Clarence Durham is survived by his brother, Dallie "D.L." Durham;
sons, Gerald Durham (Kris), Robert Durham (Janie), and Brian Durham (Sheila);
grandchildren, Stephen Durham, Robbie Durham (Danna), Katherine Smith (Caleb), Jeffrey
Durham (Courtney), Hope Worthan (Jacob), Daisy Hooter (Jake), Faith Durham, Cyera
Durham, and Donnie Durham; sixteen great-grandchildren; and numerous extended relatives
and friends; he will be deeply missed, but the legacy of his love and service to his family,
friends, community, and nation shall live on in the hearts and minds of those who were
privileged to have known and loved him.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby express heartfelt condolences on the death of Clarence
Durham, the last living LaSalle Parish World War II veteran; does hereby offer enduring
appreciation and respect for Mr. Durham's outstanding military service; and does hereby
extend sincere wishes that his family, friends, and loved ones find comfort in their shared
memories of his inspiring life.
